msgstr ""

# e7a5525957a54397876028366916c712
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSTypes.en.rst:98
msgid ""
"This set of enums represents the possible HTTP types that can be assigned"
" to an HTTP header."
msgstr ""

# 1fcb05ba87a84baba3cce8cd03f79b07
#: ../../developer-guide/api/functions/TSTypes.en.rst:101
msgid ""
"When a header is created with :func:`TSHttpHdrCreate`, it is "
"automatically assigned a type of :data:`TS_HTTP_TYPE_UNKNOWN`.  You can "
"modify the HTTP type ONCE after it the header is created, using "
":func:`TSHttpHdrTypeSet`.  After setting the HTTP type once, you cannot "
"set it again.  Use :func:`TSHttpHdrTypeGet` to obtain the "
":type:`TSHttpType` of an HTTP header."
msgstr ""

# acb6f96eb1464525860c9d8cf849c1a3
